| v15 | pilates-reformer/PR-01-base/PR-01-base-v15.scad | Superseded — fixed the v14 neck/bell gap and reduced pole_od/neck_od, but the v15 render revealed 2 new problems: neck appeared off-axis from the bell, and the neck unioned far enough into the bell to plug the bore opening (would block the 32mm bar). Fixed in v16. |
| v16 | pilates-reformer/PR-01-base/PR-01-base-v16.scad | Superseded — fixes 2 problems Janis flagged from the v15 render. Root-cause check on the "offset" issue: neck and bell were already both anchored at the same (cx,cy) — coordinate math confirms no true misalignment; the visual offset is explained entirely by the bore-plugging issue below, not a separate coordinate bug. Bore-plug fix: neck_top repositioned from v15's xbar_z+0.2 (which put ~16.7mm of neck material inside the bore's void) to xbar_z - top_bore_d/2 - neck_bore_clearance(2mm) — verified via Python this lands inside the bell's solid wall band directly under the bore, giving 5mm solid union overlap with 2mm clearance from the bore void; M6 bolt holes (still neck_h*0.3/0.7 below neck_top) land well clear of the bore automatically. DEFENSIVE GUARANTEE added: an explicit bore-envelope cylinder is now also subtracted from the neck (not just the bell), making bore clearance code-provable rather than position-tuning-dependent. pole_body() height formula updated to match the new (lower) neck_top anchor — still no visible gap there. Janis QA via F5/F6: FAIL — visible offset between neck centerline and bell bore axis still read, and the neck-bell joint read as a hard seam (two assembled components, not one casting); bolt holes also sat too close to both neck edges after v16 shortened the effective span. Fixed in v17. |
| v17 | pilates-reformer/PR-01-base/PR-01-base-v17.scad | Superseded — re-derived bell/neck axis coincidence (confirmed) and added pole_top_transition() seam blend; Janis flagged 2 ROOT-CAUSE problems from the render (bell edge-anchored not centered; D-profile not carried into neck). Fixed in v18. |
| v18 | pilates-reformer/PR-01-base/PR-01-base-v18.scad | Superseded — PROBLEM 1 fix: pole_top_bell() re-anchored from its small face to its BORE MIDPOINT (translate([cx-dir*head_h/2,cy,xbar_z])) so the bore's own center lands on the neck's centerline (x=cx) — a true T-junction, not edge-mounted; pole_top_transition()'s bell-side anchor updated to match the bell's now-shifted small face. PROBLEM 2 fix: pole_top_neck() carries pole_body()'s exact flat_x=dir*0.7*pole_r cut plane down through a new fully-D zone (d_zone_h=neck_h-neck_round_taper_h=55mm) for flush (coplanar) seating against pole_body()'s flat face, then hull()-tapers back to round over the top neck_round_taper_h=15mm (NEW global) so it still meets the round transition/bell unchanged. Bolt change: 2x M6 holes rotated from rotate([90,0,0]) (round wall) to rotate([0,90,0]) (flat D-face), Z-positions kept at neck_top-25/neck_top-50, both inside the fully-D zone and clearing bolt_edge_clearance_min (15mm TBD). Unchanged: bore diameter (33mm), bell wine-glass profile, pole_od=40mm/neck_od=47mm, pole_base_collar(), pole_wood_socket(), crossbar, latch/cam/lever mechanism (Stage 2, deferred). Brace/paren balance: 35/35, 485/485. No OpenSCAD binary in this sandbox — code-review + coordinate-math verification only. Janis F5/F6 render confirmed correct (per v19 prompt context) — both root-cause issues fixed. |
| v19 | pilates-reformer/PR-01-base/PR-01-base-v19.scad | Superseded — ITEM A: pole_top_transition() coordinate dump ONLY (diagnostic per SKILL_joint_construction.md isolation-test discipline) — module byte-identical to v18, NO geometry change. Numbers (see cc_chat_log.md): neck top cross-section round/47mm axis-Z at (cx,cy,2001.5); bell small-face round/47mm axis-X at (cx∓45,cy,2020) — same shape/size, but 90° axis-orientation mismatch + 48.65mm 3D center offset across a single hull() — this (not shape/size) is the likely facet-crease cause, flagged for Claude Web's Rule 1/2 review before the next (separate) fix prompt. ITEM B: pole_top_bell() p2 control point changed from [head_large_r*0.60,head_h*0.70] to [head_large_r*0.80,head_h*0.65] — mirrors p1's existing small-end logic, makes the large (pipe-entry) face concave/wine-glass instead of convex horn flare (Python Bezier-verified: curve_r < chord_r at all interior t). head_large_r reduced 46mm→40mm (Janis's -6mm request), still 16.5mm above head_small_r (23.5mm). Bore (33mm,X), pole_top_transition(), pole_top_neck(), bolts, neck_od all unchanged. Min wall at new large face = 23.5mm, clears 2mm project minimum. Brace/paren balance: 35/35, 512/512. No OpenSCAD binary in this sandbox — code-review + coordinate/Bezier-math verification only. Janis F5/F6 render confirmed Item B correct; transition crease flagged for v20 fix. |
| v20 | pilates-reformer/PR-01-base/PR-01-base-v20.scad | **ACTIVE** — Prompt 2/2 of isolation-test discipline (root cause identified in v19 coord dump: 90° axis-orientation mismatch, not shape/size). pole_top_transition() rebuilt as an 8-step "elbow loft": each step is a constant-d=47mm (neck_od) circular cross-section, position smoothstep-eased (t_eased=t*t*(3-2*t)) from the neck-top anchor (cx,cy,neck_top) to the bell small-face anchor (bell-side x, cy, xbar_z), rotation linearly interpolated rotate([0,90*t,0]) from 0° (neck, Z-axis/cylinder default) to 90° (bell, matching its existing rotate([0,90,0])); adjacent steps hull()'d pairwise (7 hulls) and union()'d, replacing the old single hull() that spanned the full twisted gap and produced the diagonal saddle/crease facet. Verified numerically (cc_chat_log.md): t=0 and t=7 steps match the pre-existing neck-top and bell-small-face cross-sections exactly (0mm/0° delta both ends); neck_od constant 47mm at all 8 steps, zero diameter drift; consecutive step centers 6.86-8.05mm apart (non-degenerate, no self-intersection, well under 2×radius=47mm); bore-envelope clearance computed per step, steps 5-7 legitimately sit inside the bore radius by design near the bell's small face and are still protected by the pre-existing, unchanged bore-envelope subtraction in pole_top(). DO NOT TOUCH list (bore 33mm/X, bell wine-glass profile both ends, head_large_r 40mm, head_small_r 23.5mm, pole_od 40mm, neck_od 47mm, neck_h, D-profile zone, bolt positions, pole_body(), pole_base_collar(), pole_wood_socket(), crossbar) re-verified untouched. Brace/paren balance: 36/36, 569/569. No OpenSCAD binary in this sandbox — code-review + coordinate-math verification only. Janis F5/F6 render required to confirm the diagonal crease is gone — NOT yet visually confirmed. This is Prompt 2 of 2; if QA fails, R-111 escalates directly to Janis, no 3rd attempt without new input. |

